{
  "texts": [
    "While GPT-4 does not appear capable of writing humanquality psychological papers at this time, it does appear able to write close approximations.",
    "This has significant implications for school psychology professors.",
    "As students are already using these technologies, the National Association of School Psychologists, school psychology departments and individual professors must have explicit policies in place for the use of LLMs.",
    "If professors/trainers do not wish to allow the use of GPT-4, it would appear next to impossible to easily detect their use with AI-text detectors (see Sadasivan et al.'s [2023]).",
    "Our study suggests that one approach, at least in the near term is to examine students' references, which we found were prone to errors."
  ]
}